<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1587,1683]" pageId="4" pageNumber="63">
The specific name “ 
<taxonomicName box="[429,555,1588,1612]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Sertulariidae" genus="Polysertularella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="4" pageNumber="63" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="polyseriata">
<emphasis box="[429,555,1588,1612]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="63">polyseriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”, an adjective agreeing in gender with the feminine generic name 
<taxonomicName class="Hydrozoa" family="Sertulariidae" genus="Polysertularella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="4" pageNumber="63" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="63">Polysertularella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, reflects the main morphological character of the colony structure – multi-serial arrangement of hydrothecae.
</paragraph>
